<p>The ending leaves a little to be desired, but overall I think it's pretty dang good.</p>
<p>This also introduces the concept of D.S. al Fine as a lower-level counterpoint to D.C. al Fine, the former being &quot;From the sign to Fine&quot; and the latter &quot;From the top to Fine&quot;.</p>
</div>
</div>
